Description: Fragment of hexagonal handle and attachment to wall of East Greek grey ware pottery vessel, amphora, krater, or oinochoe; plastic ring separates handle from wall; light grey fabric with limestone and mica inclusions; dark grey slip.
Curator's comments: Orientation uncertain, but more likely vertical.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.010)
